{"title":"Lads on (Grand) Tour: The 14 British and Irish riders at the Giro d’Italia 2025","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/british-riders-giro-ditalia","date":1747154490000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/british-riders-giro-ditalia\">Lads on (Grand) Tour: The 14 British and Irish riders at the Giro d’Italia 2025</a></p>\n\n<p>Grand Tours season is now well underway, with the first men’s three-weeker, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/giro-ditalia\" target=\"_blank\">Giro d’Italia</a>, having just touched down in Italy after a transit rest day following the opening weekend’s action in Albania.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It may be early days, but the general classification looks set to be a battle between Slovenia and Spain, but with a record-breaking contingent of British riders in the WorldTour this season, there are plenty of representatives from the UK and Ireland at the Giro.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s a great mix of lads too, with riders young and old, sprinters and climbers, domestiques and team leaders. Here’s the full list of who to keep track of this month.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Sam Bennett (Decathlon-AG2R La Mondiale)</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214342430.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214342430.webp 1024w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214342430-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214342430-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214342430-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214342430-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214342430-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214342430-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214342430-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption>Dario Belingheri/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This is Sam Bennett’s second Giro d’Italia. His first in 2018 was mightily successful, taking three stage wins. Now 34 years old and riding for Decathlon-AG2R La Mondiale, he has the points jersey ‘in mind’ but is primarily focussed on winning sprints.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+5\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-970x300.webp\" alt=\"Cyclist banner saying 'the finest writing and photography delivered every month, click here to subscribe'\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Mark Donovan and Tom Pidcock (Q36.5 Pro Cycling)</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/20250423FWH0194-970x647.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/20250423FWH0194-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/20250423FWH0194-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/20250423FWH0194-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/20250423FWH0194-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/20250423FWH0194-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/20250423FWH0194-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/20250423FWH0194-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/20250423FWH0194-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/20250423FWH0194-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/20250423FWH0194-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption> </figcaption><figcaption>A.S.O./Billy Ceusters</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Mark Donovan and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tom-pidcock-profile\" target=\"_blank\">Tom Pidcock</a> are making their debut appearances at the Giro d’Italia, which also marks the first Grand Tour for their Q36.5 Pro Cycling team. Marquee off-season signing Pidcock takes up the mantle as team leader with his GC bid a priority, but failing that he’ll pivot to join the rest of the team stage-hunting.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-2025-storylines\">Six Giro d’Italia 2025 storylines to follow outside of the GC</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-predictions-2025\">Cyclist’s Giro d’Italia 2025 predictions</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-favourites\">Who are the favourites for the Giro d’Italia 2025?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-and-live-stream-the-giro-ditalia\">How to watch the Giro d’Italia 2025</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">Giro d’Italia 2025 preview: Route, favourites, how to watch and start list</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Paul Double (Jayco-AlUla)</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2213945935-970x647.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2213945935-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2213945935-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2213945935-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2213945935-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2213945935-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2213945935-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2213945935-350x233.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2213945935.webp 1024w\" /><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Paul Double is one of a trio at Jayco-AlUla making their debut at the race. Double has been rising through the ranks for a number of years – he has a great story – <a href=\"https://www.cyclingweekly.com/news/latest-news/can-money-buy-you-cycling-success-370271\" target=\"_blank\">tracked by Cycling Weekly</a>, and he’s finally in his first season at WorldTour level aged 28.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Double won a stage at Coppi e Bartali this year and heads to the Giro d’Italia as part of a team looking for both stage wins and some form of GC success with Chris Harper.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Owain Doull, Darren Rafferty, James Shaw (EF Education-EasyPost)</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214842531.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214842531.webp 1024w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214842531-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214842531-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214842531-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214842531-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214842531-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214842531-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214842531-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>EF Education-EasyPost have the biggest contingent of British and Irish riders at the Giro, with a trio of them supporting leader Richard Carapaz. 2025 marks Owain Doull’s second participation in the Giro d’Italia after a DNF in 2022. The former <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/olympics\" target=\"_blank\">Olympic</a> team pursuit champion will likely be a key domestique for the team this time around.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Irish national champion Darren Rafferty is making his debut at the pro Giro having finishing second overall at the Giro Next Gen in 2023, and he’ll be looking to get Grand Tour experience as he continues his development. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also at the race for the first time is East Midlander James Shaw. He has Grand Tour experience with two participations in the Vuelta a España and one <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tour-de-france\" target=\"_blank\">Tour de France</a> in 2023, where he had a couple of strong showings in the breakaway.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ethan Hayter, James Knox (Soudal-QuickStep)</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1818\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214542912-scaled.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214542912-scaled.webp 2560w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214542912-300x213.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214542912-970x689.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214542912-768x546.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214542912-1536x1091.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214542912-2048x1455.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214542912-120x86.webp 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214542912-350x250.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214542912-750x533.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214542912-1140x810.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214542912-190x136.webp 190w\" /><figcaption>Dario Belingheri/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Plans can change in the blink of an eye. Ethan Hayter and James Knox were originally pencilled in to help Mikel Landa on GC for Soudal-QuickStep, but with the Spaniard now out of the race, their focus switches to helping sprinter Paul Magnier and getting into breakaways.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Max Poole (Picnic-PostNL)</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/GettyImages-2169297961-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/GettyImages-2169297961-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/GettyImages-2169297961-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/GettyImages-2169297961-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/GettyImages-2169297961-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/GettyImages-2169297961-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/GettyImages-2169297961-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/GettyImages-2169297961-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/GettyImages-2169297961-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/GettyImages-2169297961-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/09/GettyImages-2169297961-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Dario Belingheri/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With XDS-Astana breathing down Picnic-PostNL’s neck in the relegation battle, the team are desperate to bag some points to avoid the drop. Max Poole came close on multiple stages at the Vuelta a España last season, making the podium four times, and is set to have a go at the GC for the first time at this Giro.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Josh Tarling, Ben Turner (Ineos Grenadiers)</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-1640050499-scaled.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-1640050499-scaled.webp 2560w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-1640050499-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-1640050499-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-1640050499-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-1640050499-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-1640050499-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-1640050499-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-1640050499-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-1640050499-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-1640050499-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-1640050499-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption>Bas Czerwinski/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Josh Tarling was always going to be the one to watch at this Giro’s time-trials and he didn’t disappoint on the first, winning Stage 2 by a second for his first Grand Tour stage victory. His Ineos teammate Ben Turner will be a key domestique for Egan Bernal and Thymen Arensman, but the Doncaster man also looks to have been given the green light to contest sprints too.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Adam Yates (UAE Team Emirates XRG)</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-27T102452.048-970x647.png\" alt=\"adam yates\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-27T102452.048-970x646.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-27T102452.048-300x200.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-27T102452.048-768x512.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-27T102452.048-1536x1024.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-27T102452.048-750x500.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-27T102452.048-1140x760.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-27T102452.048-465x310.png 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-27T102452.048-620x413.png 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-27T102452.048-350x233.png 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-27T102452.048.png 1800w\" /><figcaption>Unipublic/Sprint Cycling Agency</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Adam Yates is sharing UAE leadership duties at this race with Juan Ayuso. This is Yates’ second Giro d’Italia, his first coming back in 2017 when he finished ninth overall. He’ll be hoping to either improve his best result in a Grand Tour – third at the Tour de France in 2023 – or help Ayuso if he takes the race lead.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yates is also looking to complete his set of Grand Tour stage wins having won at both the Tour and the Vuelta. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Simon Yates (Visma-Lease a Bike)</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214362396-scaled.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214362396-scaled.webp 2560w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214362396-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214362396-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214362396-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214362396-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214362396-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214362396-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214362396-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214362396-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214362396-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/05/GettyImages-2214362396-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption>Dario Belingheri/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The other Yates twin is also in a lead role for his team Visma-Lease a Bike. A Grand Tour winner at the Vuelta a España in 2018, he has also won six Giro stages between 2018 and 2022.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simon finished on the Giro podium in 2021 and new team Visma-Lease a Bike will hoping for a similar result this time around.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/british-riders-giro-ditalia\">Lads on (Grand) Tour: The 14 British and Irish riders at the Giro d’Italia 2025</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Robyn Davidson &#124; Editorial Assistant","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"a765adf412951b69b95839a8107d7156c527ef8cb41d29ae81613ffd46348761","category":"Cycling"}